<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="367" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,799,824]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from Latin adjective ‘spinosus’ (thorny, prickly) referring to its pygofer process possess with several stout spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
