<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="367" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,908,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Dworakowska, 1979" authorityName="Dworakowska" authorityYear="1979" box="[670,1090,908,933]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ziczacella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="katoi">
<emphasis box="[670,849,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Ziczacella katoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dworakowska, I." box="[858,1090,908,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref4879" refString="Dworakowska, I. (1979) On some Erythroneurini from Vietnam (Typhlocybinae, Cicadellidae). Annotationes Zoologicae et Botanicae, 131, 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="1979">Dworakowska, 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished from the latter by the pygofer process of the male with 5 sharp spines on the dorsal surface, and with a longer and narrower apex; and by the acuminate (rather than obliquely truncate) apex of the aedeagus in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
